						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ: Vīranārāyaṇaṉ (?) (1139-49 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>This very much damaged inscription records an order of the king relating to the grant of land and certain levies probably for raising and tending a flowergarden. The other details are lost. </p>						

